TH "SIMPLE_SHELL" "ALX" "0x16. C - Simple Shell" "19" "October 2023"
.SH NAME
.B shellby\[fR] \- simple UNIX Command line interpreter
.SH AUTHORS
Ikechukwu Vincent, Cambridge MM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include \shell.h\
.sp
.B int hsh(void)
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]simple_shell\f[R]  a Command language interpreter to execute
commands interactively and non\-interactively.
Reads the commands form the standard input.
.SH INVOCATION
.PP
To use the simple_shell, compile \f[I].c files and output in a file hsh
$ gcc \-Wall \-Werror \-Wextra \-pendatic \f[R].c \-0 hsh
\f[B]simple_shell\f[R] can be run interactively by: $ ./hsh
\f[B]simple_shell\f[R] can be run non\-interactively by: $ echo `ls' |
\&./hsh
.SH BUGS
.PP
Report bugs experienced.
.SH EXIT
.PP
The exit command terminates the process(es) and closes Shell.
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
bash(1)

